#: ../../child-issue-template.md:1
msgid ""
"This issue is for translating **[`FILENAME`](FILE_URL)** into Spanish. It"
" is one part of the larger effort tracked in the main issue: "
"MAIN_ISSUE_URL. Start there if you want the full picture and the setup "
"steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:3
msgid ""
"Thank you for helping! If this is your first open source contribution, "
"you are in the right place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:5
msgid ""
"If you are working in one of our development sprints at a conference, "
"someone from the pyOpenSci team will be available to help you get set up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:7
msgid "Claim your lines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:9
msgid ""
"To keep our work from overlapping, claim a range of lines before you "
"start:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:11
msgid "Read the comments below to see which lines are already taken."
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:12
msgid "Add a comment with the lines you will translate. You can copy this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:13
msgid "I'm working on lines 1–100."
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:14
msgid "When your part is ready, open a Pull Request and link back to this issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:16
msgid ""
"You can see line numbers when you open the file on GitHub. If you are not"
" sure how much you can take on, start with a small range. You can always "
"claim more later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:18
msgid ""
"When you link this issue from your Pull Request, please write `Part of "
"#ISSUE_NUMBER` rather than `Closes #ISSUE_NUMBER`. Several people are "
"translating this file, so it should stay open until every line is done."
msgstr ""

