#: ../../child-issue-template.md:27
msgid "This file, as of STATS_DATE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../child-issue-template.md:29
msgid ""
"**If you come across a string marked `fuzzy`**, it already has a Spanish "
"translation, but that translation needs a second look to confirm it is "
"correct. Usually this is because the English text changed after the "
"string was translated, though a string can be marked fuzzy for other "
"reasons too. Compare the translation against the English text above it. "
"If it still says the right thing, simply remove the line with the "
"**fuzzy** tag. If it does not, rewrite it and then remove the tag. The "
"Translation Guide explains this further in [What happens when a string "
"has changed in the original English text](https://www.pyopensci.org"
"/python-package-guide/TRANSLATING.html#what-happens-when-a-string-has-"
"changed-in-the-original-english-text)."
msgstr ""

